The paper deals with the problem of online stochastic bipartite matching, which involves allocating resources (display ads) to users (nodes) in an online setting. This problem is closely related to load balancing and network flow problems, which are typically studied in the cs.DS and cs.NW sub-categories. The paper also uses techniques from game theory and approximation algorithms, which are studied in the cs.GT sub-category. Information theory (cs.IT) is also relevant, as the paper deals with the problem of approximating the optimal solution under uncertainty. Finally, the paper uses probabilistic and statistical techniques to analyze the performance of the algorithm, which are studied in the cs.LG and cs.SI sub-categories.
